caption: Incredible food and really good service ! Had the vegetarian plate, highly recommended.
Pretty solid food at decent prices. I'm not looking for 5-star dining, just some place to get some shwarma. Hummus is good and it's a decent hole-in-the-wall neighborhood joint.
Been coming here over 30yrs. Authentic food has gone down a bit in taste still worth it

terrible service. would give 0 if possible.    smells inside like rancid burnt oil.   while  just inside, i asked if shawarma platter could have salad as 1 of its 2 sides... counterman just hands me the menu.   menu says choice of sides. sigh.   i converse with him, he speaks just fine but won't answer the question:  he says he cannot say, and points to the menu.  sigh.  as i want to keep small places open, i go to Broadway Pizza next door, which is clean & helpful hardworking guys.   spend your $ here.

I mean its a great local spot. It may not look appealing from the outside however the food is amazing!!!!! Great flavor and spice! Shawarma platter! A+++ grade. Try it out. Got a 4 because i think the falafel could be much better. However it did have amazing flavor. Check them out.
Great food, nice And friendly workers. Very healthy and clean.

The owner, a small old man, is a kind good person. However, his guy on the grill is DISGUSTING. He is nasty and rude and talks to you like you're bothering him, and I am now NEVER COMING BACK because of this employee.
Great falafel. Very generous size sandwich
Spent 30 minutes looking for a good sandwich in the Upper West Side and this place knocked it out the park

This place used to be so good. The service is horrendous! They have to get a new guy on the grill! His attitude is the worst! I asked for hot sauce and white sauce.....and he was bothered! Get the hell out of here! I come to find out that he didn't put anything on it!! Avoid this place at all costs! Hey owner, you need to clean house!!!
Excellent chicken and lamb shawarma platter. Good falafel and fresh salad. One of the best Mediterranean restaurant in Upper West Side. Definitely will come back here again and again
Great hole in the wall lunch spot. It’s been around for a long time.
Awesome food
Great food, with good earnest people. These hole in the wall locations make NYC special. support them.

Nice neighborhood spot: Excellent falafel balls, salads were fresh, and the owner was very friendly. I would skip the pita bread next time though.  I ate here in 2000, this place has been around for at least 20 years.
Amazing Gyros

Wow, this restaurant is still in business. I haven’t been there in years. My brother lived across the street on 102 street. I would go whenever I would visit. I  definitely agree it’s a fantastic restaurant.
Excellent Mediterranean food! Absolutely recommendable here in New York . High quality service and fast service. Best overall experience so far!

Amazing cardamom-flavored falafel and decent hummus. Everything else is terrible. Service is painfully slow, meat tasted somehow fake and gristly at the same time, and the Turkish coffee was basically brown water. Not recommended.
The chicken falafel sandwich is where its at!
You can find the halal middle eastern food at this place
Order their chicken platter with onions all the time. The hummus is excellent. For basic go to Middle Eastern food,  you cannot go wrong. As for their homemade hot sauce.

I have been coming here for more than 20 years when  I first moved to the neighborhood. I've moved since then but every time I come home, I stop in here for a falafel with extra tahini sauce. They are dedicated to their craft here and it shows I  everything you eat. They still make their sandwiches in the round pitas instead of the ever trendy wraps that you find these days. They drop the falafel in the fryer after I place my order so I know it's fresh every time. It's a small place so I wouldn't plan to.wat here if you're with a group but carry our is done so well that your order will hold up until you can sink your teeth into it. I ate here because i was alone and the service was kind and friendly as per their usual. If you like this kind if fare, then they are a must do when on the Upper West Side.

I am changing my very low review to a high one based on excellent customer service. I have been frequenting this restaurant for nearly 25 years, and while falafels are undoubtedly better in Amsterdam, the ones here are pretty darn good. Baba ghanoush and hummus also delicious. I had a very bad experience late one night and food was not delivered. However, I went in the next day to complain and not only was I greeted warmly as a long-time customer, but I was given a heartfelt apology and a reasonable explanation, as well as a good plan for such a kerfuffle not to happen again ( and it hasn’t). I also got a free meal for myself and a friend and a warm invite to return ( and I have—many times yummmmmmm). This is one of my all-time fave neighborhood spots. Yes I was let down once but every single other experience at Jerusalem restaurant has been stupendous. A real winner.
They make one of the best falafel I've tasted. When I'm in the neighborhood I make an effort to get my falafel in a pita.
Darn good felafel.
I love thier falafels!
Decent Shawermas.
Best falafel and hummus ever.

Tried lamb sandwich & tea for dinner. I asked something warm and the guy suggested meat sandwiches. Lamb is bit fatty and juicy ,so it’s easy to chew . And various veggies, falafel , and fumes are in it. Small size was enough for me. Their tea has cardamons!
Use to be better. But I love the"dive"feel.
Food is good, i highly recommend it !

The guy that works there is horrible, such a bad attitude. All the freaking time, the food is good. Just the worker who takes orders seems like he hates his job. Good food , terrible customer service.
Disgusting food:(((

Great spot if you’re ordering for a group of people, the packaging was very portable and convenient. The food was AMAZING! I had the vegetarian combo (falafel, hummus, babaganoush, tabbouch salad served with pita) and it was delicious! Prices were unbeatable! Will be back for sure

(Translated by Google) Medium flavor kebab, strange ingredients. Pretty expensive. You will definitely eat better in Poland :-)  (Original) Kebab średni w smaku, dziwne składniki. Dosyć drogo. Na pewno w Polsce zje się lepsze :-)
Great food and staff.
Tasty food at a good price

This place is da bomb. They're lamb and chicken shwarmas are grilled to perfection. They're salad bar is delicious with ecentric flavors like beats green peppers and hummus. Also, must try their baklava!
AMAZING BAKLAVA! Love the food. Tasty, filling, and decent prices. The few times I have eaten there have made it a fave for me.

Good food, which makes it a shame that the place consistently has bad service.  They clearly let their regulars budge in line.  However good the food is, it is not good enough to be treated as a second class customer.
Good food. Great place for vegetarian and vegan people. Not the best customer service though
Hole in the wall falafel joint w excellent veggie foods.Meat just ok.Falafel and baba gounesh delish!
Everyone was friendly and accommodating and the food was great
Delicious, authentic and fast
Love it. So amazing.love the sandwiches

No stars. The worst Israeli/Middle Eastern food ever. Stay away.  The lamb shawarma had two bit of lamb and some falafel stuck inand wasn't warm. The Jerusalem plate with babaganou and hummus was bad. The pita bread was stale. Stay away.
Fantastic little spot for shawarma. Love the free Pita chips and chili oil as you wait.
Good food clean and good  quality good price
(Translated by Google) Small but cozy place, friendly people and very rich food  (Original) Lugar pequeño pero acogedor, gente amable y muy rica comida

From the moment I walked in and asked about the menu items, the guy taking my order had a bad attitude and seemed to have trouble understanding me. The hummus plate I ended up getting made no sense, it was all hummus and some lettuce tomato. The dish would make so much more sense to add a third item, but he wants to charge me to add anything else to it, per piece mind you. This might as well be a side dish. He was rude and kept arguing with me, poor customer service skills. The hummus itself was just okay. This place is not authentic Israeli/Middle Eastern, and it's now on my Do Not Go list. I have to actually go buy a real dinner now...
Great falalel served with humus and nice service.
Yummy and healthy food!  Great place for vegan or vegetarian eaters.  Salads can be made any way you like, wraps are delicious as well as their lentil soup!  Also try the baklava...two thumbs up!!
I've had the lunch time special wrap and plate. The chicken is good but the rest is OK. The hummus is not good at all.

This place is fine, decent food (nothing stood out in either a good or bad way) at decent prices. They were about to re-heat a baklava for me in the microwave but I told them to forget it, I couldn't believe that's how they re-heat. The falafel and shwarma was good though and the veggies were fresh enough. Overall, the epitome of a 3 star restaurant, but if you're in the area and want middle eastern, it will do.

Good place to grab a quick falafel sandwich but nothing special. This is store-bought pita bread and some greens that have been sitting in the dairy case. Can't be compared with say Taim as a destination restaurant, so I give it 3 stars as solid but not memorable.
Good food. Probably one of the only joints to serve Middle Eastern Cuisine.
Fresh falafel with good hummus served a ton of different ways. Best in the area for Middle Eastern food.
Sit by the laminated picture of the Dome of the Rock and enjoy great Mediterranean food.
Food lacks taste. Roaches and flies in the kitchen. Overcooked my falafel. Dolmas had no taste. Side orders are overpriced.

THREW UP ALL NIGHT from this dump. bad food, terrible service, never coming back Overpriced. Terrible atmosphere. Never got our soda and the best thing we had were the fries. Never again.  STAY FAR FAR AWAY

I have been away from New York for 11 years and I STILL remember the taste of their shawarma and falafell sandwiches!  Pocket sized lunch counter with big flavor served with little bowls of chili sauce.  Soooo good.
Seriously the best falafel on the upper west side, maybe Manhattan, I haven't tried them all.  Great service, great food, great location.

Terrible. I was there two weeks ago on a visit to NY City. I read the reviews about this place and decided to give a try.  The place was dirty and extremely hot. The food was bad. I would never go back there again.
This place is really good. Great place for fast and inexpensive food, snacks usually provided while you wait for  your order.
